data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` code **won't compile**. Replace the entire block:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — no expression tree needed
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The API now accepts `Action<SetPropertyCalls<Blog>>` instead of `Expression<Func<…>>`, so conditionals work natively.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Your `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` will get auto-generated suffixes (e.g. `Street1`). Pin existing names:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
        a.Property(x => x.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was `BillingAddress_City`, now becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. Pin it:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, a =>
        a.Property(x => x.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
```

Without explicit `HasColumnName`, EF will generate a migration renaming these columns.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL for safe logging
    { /* logging — use logCommandText instead of command.CommandText
         if you want constants redacted */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on that interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
